One of the daughters of President Muhammadu Buhari, Hanan is set to marry Mohammed Turad, a special adviser to former Lagos State governor and current Minister of Works, Babatunde Fashola. According to SR, Hunan Buhari and Mohammed Turad, marriage is set to take place on September 4, 2020. The wedding will be held inside the Aso Rock Villa and has been dubbed as ‘The First wedding’, being the first-ever wedding to happen in the Aso Rock Villa. Mohammed Turad is the son of a former lawmaker, Alhaji Mahmud Sani Sha’aban, who represented Zaria in the House of Representatives from May 2003 to May 2007. Sha’aban is also a former governorship candidate in Kaduna State under the defunct Action Congress of Nigeria. Source ABUJA – President Muhammadu Buhari has announced the first set of appointments into his administration. The President on Sunday evening, May 31, named Mr Femi Adesina and Mal. Garba Shehu as his spokesmen. Mr. Femi Adesina will serve as Special Adviser (Media and Publicity) while Mallam Garba Shehu will be… May 31, 2015 In "News" •Hanan Buhari with Bauchi State First Lady, Dr. Aisha Bala Mohammed and other officials Hanan Buhari, the youngest daughter of President Muhammadu Buhari, on Thursday visited Bauchi on a presidential jet to attend a special durbar ceremony organised in her honour by the Emir of Bauchi, Rilwanu Adamu, at his… January 11, 2020 In "News" A debate has been raging on social media following the decision of President Muhammadu Buhari to allow his daughter, Hanan Buhari, to use the Presidential jet. This is despite complaints by Nigerians that the budget of N8.5bn for the Presidential jets in the 2020 budget is too high. Hanan, according… January 11, 2020 In "Metro"